{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 02:12:01.814747", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 4‑tier Clos with EBGP between tiers; each leaf should originate only its directly connected service subnet 10.<pod>.<idx>.0/24. Client_0 (192.168.0.2/24) uses DNS at 10.0.0.2 (dns_pod0). Target service: webserver0_pod0 at 10.0.1.2:80 (python http.server).\\n\\nObserved Symptoms (from client_0)\\n- DNS resolution: web0.pod0 resolves to 10.0.1.2 (A record).\\n- HTTP:\\n  - curl http://web0.pod0 returns http_code:000 (connection failed).\\n  - curl http://10.0.1.2 succeeds quickly (~1–2 ms).\\n- ICMP: ping 10.0.0.2 (DNS) and 10.0.1.2 (web) both succeed (0% loss, ~1–3 ms RTT).\\n- Traceroute to 10.0.1.2 shows path via 192.168.0.1 (super spine), then destination (intermediate hops may not reply to TTL-exceeded).\\n\\nControl Plane Health\\n- All BGP sessions across leaves, spines, and super‑spine are up; prefixes widely exchanged; ECMP active where expected.\\n\\nCritical Anomaly Detected (Routing)\\n- A more-specific route 10.0.1.0/25 is being originated and advertised by spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101). This is incorrect: spines should only transit, not originate tenant subnets.\\n  - spine_router_0_1 running-config:\\n    - interface lo has ip address 10.0.1.0/25\\n    - router bgp 65101 advertises network 10.0.1.0/25\\n  - Routing tables confirm propagation and preference of the /25:\\n    - spine_router_0_1: C>* 10.0.1.0/25 is directly connected, lo\\n    - super_spine_router_0: B>* 10.0.1.0/25 via 172.16.0.3 (spine_router_0_1)\\n    - spine_router_0_0: has 10.0.1.0/25 via multiple peers (including spine_router_0_1)\\n    - leaf_router_0_0: B>* 10.0.1.0/25 via 172.16.0.144 (to spine_router_0_1)\\n    - leaf_router_0_1 (which directly connects 10.0.1.0/24): still learns B>* 10.0.1.0/25 via 172.16.0.146 (to spine_router_0_1), in addition to its connected 10.0.1.0/24\\n- Because 10.0.1.2 lies within 10.0.1.0/25, longest‑prefix match causes traffic for lower-half addresses of that /24 to be attracted to spine_router_0_1. Since this /25 is configured on spine’s loopback (not the leaf-facing interface), packets are effectively sinkholed/blackholed at the spine.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- This misadvertised /25 can blackhole traffic destined to 10.0.1.0–10.0.1.127 from elsewhere in the fabric (including from the super‑spine), resulting in intermittent or complete loss depending on path selection.\\n- The client test results are consistent with a routing anomaly:\\n  - Name resolves to 10.0.1.2 (inside the hijacked /25) and HTTP by name fails (http_code 000).\\n  - Direct HTTP to 10.0.1.2 sometimes succeeds from client_0, suggesting path variability or differences in how flows are forwarded/observed; however, presence of the more‑specific route at the super‑spine indicates high risk of blackhole on that path.\\n\\nNon‑routing Checks\\n- DNS server (dns_pod0) is listening on 10.0.0.2:53 and 127.0.0.1:53; service appears up.\\n- Web server (webserver0_pod0) is listening on 0.0.0.0:80; service responds when reached by IP.\\n- Host IP/gateway configurations are correct.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: spine_router_0_1.\\n- Faulty configuration elements:\\n  - Loopback address set to 10.0.1.0/25.\\n  - BGP “network 10.0.1.0/25” advertising this tenant prefix from the spine.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Route hijack via unintended advertisement of a more-specific service subnet (10.0.1.0/25) by a spine. This violates the Clos EBGP design intent (only leaves originate tenant /24s) and causes blackholing of traffic within that more-specific prefix.\\n\\nKey Evidence (commands -> findings)\\n- on spine_router_0_1: show running-config -> interface lo ip 10.0.1.0/25; router bgp 65101 network 10.0.1.0/25\\n- on super_spine_router_0: show ip route 10.0.1.0/25 -> B>* via 172.16.0.3\\n- on leaf_router_0_1: show ip route 10.0.1.0/25 -> B>* via 172.16.0.146 (despite connected 10.0.1.0/24)\\n- client_0: dig web0.pod0 -> 10.0.1.2; curl http://web0.pod0 -> http_code:000; curl http://10.0.1.2 -> success\\n\\nOverall Assessment\\n- Control plane is up but the network is not healthy due to a critical routing misconfiguration at spine_router_0_1 that injects a more-specific tenant prefix, leading to blackholing and service access failures for web0.pod0., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='44078a2c-4f6e-4d1b-9906-0330e392c01f'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
